name: Downtown Women's Center
review_text: I really have to hand it to Mrs more I was homeless almost 10 yrs she got me a please in two days. She is the best. I have to rate her a 5 yes a 1 for day room employees are very mean and Melisa who has been management in kitchen for five years is very rude and mean to homeless women I am speaking for all homeless women Melisa stated"she is not obligated to give second on food,"  but yet we see it given to employee's in stead of homeless women that live in the street. Also they give it for snack the next day.  I can't believe we'll we are sitting eating we witness so many donation coming in back packs full of things for women us never are given to us. I will make sure each person who donates to women's center will be told we do not get donations. Also Melisa manager of kitchen will be written up and. Document all encounters and photos of how she manages and treats homeless women.

So if youâ€™re donating to this nonprofit you are donating to a great organization Thank you womenâ€™s center for all you do for us women!

name: Downtown Women's Center
review_text: I give it one star for being a safe place to eat and shower. They make u wait a month or two for a caseworker if they don't know u. If they know you from their hood or if they where in the program with you from their past lives, then they make sure you get housing and other resources. They talk to people really rude and swear they to busy to assist. Donations they have but say they don't. My caseworker still haven't called and when I first met her she lied and said she been looking for me. Just to try to schedule me another intake for two weeks of meeting her.

name: Downtown Women's Center
review_text: Why is it that no one answers telephone lines or the messages left?  voice mail full. why are you so picky ( look at Goodwill)  you have several security guards that can easily accept donations at gate instead one need to schedule an appointment?  Come on you you act as if are asking you for favors.  people need help why do donors have to beg to donate ? pffff your staff isn't as nice as one would think . Thee people are homeless depressive, lonely in many cases, they need love understanding ad patience overall. and your staff isn't any of that.  i have tried contacting several of your staff for months left messages an no none has ever return any of my calls since the Spring. what does this tell you? not cool! Seems many are there for the paycheck no sympathy or car for the lonely and homeless.

name: Downtown Women's Center

The Downtown Womenâ€™s Center assisted me in finding an apartment when I was in jeopardy of losing my voucher. Here is a picture of me signing my rental agreement. Iâ€™m still here today in 2022. It didnâ€™t stop there. They blessed me with pots and pans, pillows, and other miscellaneous items. Til this day I am still connected with my caseworker and she calls me each month to make sure Iâ€™m doing well and to see if I have any new concerns. In fact sheâ€™s assisting me with a new concern that I have now. Downtown Womenâ€™s Center has been a total blessing to me especially during this time of covid-19. name: Downtown Women's Center
review_text: The representatives (one was named Ann and the other one was Vivian or something like that) on the phone are TERRIBLE. I setup an appointment with them last week, and was calling in advance to verify the time, and the whole time they were trying to disregard everything I was saying. I called at 8:00am, and the representative said that for whatever reason, she couldnâ€™t find my appointment and she wouldnâ€™t have the ability to look up my information without her manager, then told me to call about an hour later. I called back an hour later, and there was a new person, and instead of verifying  with the lady that was previously on the phone with me, she decided to argue with me and then refer me somewhere else. Then the first woman went up to her and said no she did call, but THEN  told me they have no appointment setup for me at all. They were very unprofessional on the phone, and thereâ€™s clearly a lack of communication between the staff. Even while I was talking she kept interrupting me, without really trying to hear what I was saying.

name: Downtown Women's Center
review_text:
This place helps whom they choose. There's not a lick of respect for the women in need. It's hard to give respect when the staff treats you akin to a 2nd class citizen. In order to get respect, you need to give it. The females in charge of this center need further training. Most are rude, talk down to the clients as if they were matrons in a penal institution. Don't even think about asking questions; the one that thinks she's a male is unnecessarily rude & repugnant!!! She's obviously feeling bad about self, then wants to push her BS onto others. She needs 2b fired like yesterday....
You get information that's outdated about housing, they lie like a rug. Many of the inept staff have issues of a serious magnitude & shouldn't be here.... I'd recommend others to go there & experience the ongoing nightmare for themselves... If you're 'cute', maybe your chance for housing may be a little better.... I also have credible info from a credible person that they have apartments right there up the stairs; however, the staff will not let the clients be privy to this. They're always sitting up vetting ppl, trying to take your inventory. Whom vetted them?? ðŸ˜ ðŸ˜ 
I just think it's terrible to be able to assist ppl, & you don't!!!
